## Writing Guidelines

### Do's

- ✓ Interpret findings in context
- ✓ Compare with previous work
- ✓ Discuss implications and significance
- ✓ Acknowledge limitations honestly
- ✓ Suggest specific future directions
- ✓ Use hedging language appropriately
- ✓ Balance enthusiasm with objectivity
- ✓ Cite relevant literature

### Don'ts

- ✗ Repeat Results section verbatim
- ✗ Introduce new results
- ✗ Overstate conclusions
- ✗ Ignore contradictory findings
- ✗ Be overly apologetic about limitations
- ✗ Make unsupported claims
- ✗ Use vague language ("interesting", "important")
- ✗ End with weak conclusions

